afani, and other writers to trace how Palestinians have represented their experience of home and exile since the First World War. This unique blending of cultural geography and literary analysis opens an unusual window on the struggle between these two peoples over a land that both divides them and brings them together.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aArabic literaturey1801-xHistory and criticism. 0aArabic literaturezPalestinexHistory and criticism. 0aGeographical perception in literature. 0aPalestinian Arabs - Ethnic identity. 0aPalestinian ArabsxEthnic identity. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292761674423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292761674/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK